ascisvg
-----------------

This is a modified version of the ASCIIsvg editor from: 
http://www1.chapman.edu/~jipsen/svg/asciisvgeditor.html

==========================================================
ASCII -> SVG PIPELINE
==========================================================

Accepts an ASCII file, and creates a SVG file.

Files:

	> SvgCanvas.py (class definition)
	> ascii_to_svg.py

LINUX Command Example:

	> python ascii_to_svg.py < ../files/ascii/file.ascsvg > ../files/svg/file.svg

==========================================================
SVG -> PNG PIPELINE
==========================================================

Accepts a SVG file, and creates a PNG file.

Files:

	> SvgCanvas.py (class definition)
	> svg_to_png.py

LINUX Command Example:

	> python svg_to_png.py < ../files/svg/file.svg > ../files/png/file.png

==========================================================
DEMO
==========================================================

Generating an HTML file with PNG vs SVG comparison:

Files:

	> SvgCanvas.py (class definition)
	> ./files/ (folder for ascii/svg/png files)
	> demo.py (generation of the files)
	> demo.html (output HTML file)

LINUX Command Example:

	> python demo.py

